explanation: The solution uses a two-pointer technique to track the current position in s1 and s2. It maintains a count of how many times s2 has been fully matched within the repetitions of s1. It also keeps track of the next index in s2 for each repetition of s1 to detect cycles and optimize the count for large n1.

